Video 10 — While Loops

Overview:
while loops execute code repeatedly as long as a condition is true.

Key Concepts:

Condition must eventually become false to avoid infinite loops
Useful for event-driven or interactive programs

Example:

i = 0
while i < 5:
    print(i)
    i += 1

Practical Insights:

Useful for repeating tasks until a condition changes
Combine with break and continue for more control
